						               													<description>Zombeja! Ovella! is Finnish language storytelling boardgame for 3-6 players, One game takes about 30 minutes per player.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Like in most traditional roleplaying games each session starts with creation of character concept. Zombeja! Ovella! utilizes &amp;quot;charactersticks&amp;quot;, short wooden sticks with different qualities like personality types and generalizations printed on them to create instant stereotypes suited for genre.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game combines competitive and co-operative play elements in storytelling to produce a structured roleplaying exercise that simulates thematic elements of survival horror movies.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players have to create conflict of interest to eliminate other players and to advance their own position on the board. Co-operation of others is required to survive but some need to be sacrificed.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Originally a free mini-game with issue #8 of Finnish language roleplaying games magazine Roolipelaaja the game was released later packaged in VHS tape case to make it look indie zombie flick.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Zombeja! Ovella! is predecessor to English language game  Zombie Cinema which essentially streamlined version of it.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
